dialogs.original: These letters give, Iago, to the pilot,    And by him do my duties to the senate.    That done, I will be walking on the works,    Repair there to me.
dialogs.translated: Iago, give these letters to the captain of my ship, and tell him to extend my greetings to the senate back in Venice. Once that is done, come find me where I will be walking atop the walls.

dialogs.original: Well, my good lord, Ill do t.
dialogs.translated: Very well, my good lord. I'll do it.

dialogs.original: This fortification, gentlemen, shall we see t?
dialogs.translated: Well then, gentlemen, shall we go see the walls of this fort?
